        <title>PROPELLER SHAFT</title>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>GENERAL</title>
                <para>A propeller shaft is a cylindrical assembly used to transmit torque from the transmission to the
                    axle by rotation.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <title>Propeller Shaft Components</title>Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0600101">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    to identify propeller shaft components.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0600101" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0600101" filename="../figg06/G0600101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="514px" scalefitheight="392px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Propeller Shaft Components</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. FLANGE YOKE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SLIP YOKE</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. SLIP SHAFT</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. BEARING CAP</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. CROSS</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. TUBING</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. TUBE YOKE</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. END YOKE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
